3. Normalization 

2. Problem Statement

Consider an unnormalized table storing student and department details.

3. Unnormalized Table
CREATE TABLE Student_Un (
    RollNo INT,
    Name VARCHAR(30),
    Dept VARCHAR(10),
    DeptHOD VARCHAR(30)
);
4. Insert Sample Data
INSERT INTO Student_Un VALUES (101, 'Ravi', 'CSE', 'Kumar');
INSERT INTO Student_Un VALUES (102, 'Anu', 'ECE', 'Ramesh');
INSERT INTO Student_Un VALUES (103, 'Kiran', 'CSE', 'Kumar');
5. Problem (Before Normalization)
Redundancy: DeptHOD repeated multiple times
Update anomaly: If HOD changes, update multiple rows
Deletion anomaly: Deleting last student removes dept info
6. Normalization to 3NF
Step 1: Create Student Table
CREATE TABLE Student (
    RollNo INT PRIMARY KEY,
    Name VARCHAR(30),
    Dept VARCHAR(10)
);
Step 2: Create Department Table
CREATE TABLE Department (
    Dept VARCHAR(10) PRIMARY KEY,
    DeptHOD VARCHAR(30)
);
7. Insert Data into Normalized Tables
